Jean-Pierre Balous has been granted bail. He is the leader of one of the refugee factions in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - The leader of one of the refugee factions in Cape Town has been granted bail of R2,000. Jean-Pierre Balous faces multiple counts of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm, as well as a charge of theft. READ: No bail for refugee leader Balous was released after his asylum-seeker documents and place of residence were verified. His movements in the CBD will be restricted. READ: No agreement on Cape Town refugees “Nothing has changed. You can’t change the ideology," Balous said after his release. "People are still suffering. I am innocent, 100 percent.” As the leader of one of the factions, Balous will only be allowed to enter the CBD to attend meetings.